[FONT=Trebuchet MS][COLOR=#4993c5][SIZE=7][B]Staff Roles[/B][/SIZE][/COLOR] [B](Sorted by rank)[/B][/FONT]
[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS]-------------------------------------------------------
[SIZE=6][COLOR=#ffa64d]Owner[/COLOR][/SIZE]
The proprietor of the entire network.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Their role is to manage the community and network as a whole. This includes staff, payments, and any other services. The Owner does not manage every aspect of the community, rather watching over the various matters and issues handled by other Staff Members.[/FONT]
[/LIST]

[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#ffa64d]Head Administrator[/COLOR][/SIZE]
Manager of the Administration.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Their role is to manage staff, focusing on the Administration. They will complete various tasks within the community, including promotions, demotions and staff applications. Furthermore, they will have access to a wide range of community utilities in order to resolve most issues, including forums and servers.[/FONT]
[/LIST]

[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#ffa64d]Administrators[/COLOR][/SIZE]
Manages servers and stability.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Their role is to maintain the servers, forums and other network services. This includes configuration, game play improvement, monitoring content, resolving bugs and more. This rank will also discuss various ideas within the Staff Team and may be included in different community projects.[/FONT]
[/LIST]

[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#ffa64d]Senior Moderators[/COLOR][/SIZE]
Manager of their server and staff.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Senior Moderators will have been assigned to a server, just like Moderators. Their duty is to watch over the Moderators and assist them with their duties. They will also have much input on the staff applications which are associated with their server. Senior Moderators have a wide knowledge of the server they play on and can assist both players and staff with this information. This role will also aid in making these staff members more aware of Administrator duties and teach them so they can eventually become part of the Administration.[/FONT]
[/LIST]

[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#ffa64d]Moderators[/COLOR][/SIZE]
Maintaining and moderating community content.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Their role is to provide support to the community, moderate forums and in-game chat, investigate various incidents and dealing appropriate punishment, reporting bugs and notifying higher staff of appropriate situations and server downtime. Furthermore, Moderators will attempt to provide the highest quality support to our community as possible, even if they arenâ€™t able to directly resolve the issue. Moderators are assigned to a specific server which they must moderate on, however they can also help out on other servers as well.[/FONT]
[/LIST]

[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#ffa64d]Trial Moderators[/COLOR][/SIZE]
Providing assistance to both players and staff.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Their role is to provide basic support to the community and assist staff where possible. This may include investigating basic incidents, helping players, reporting bugs and notifying higher staff for all situations and any server downtime which occurs. This rank is the predecessor to the Moderator rank, and is used to trial new Staff Members. Trial Moderators are assigned to a specific server which they must moderate on, however they can also help out on other servers as well.[/FONT]
[/LIST]


[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=7][COLOR=#4993c5]Community Roles[/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT]
[COLOR=rgb(0, 0, 0)][FONT=Trebuchet MS]-------------------------------------------------------[/FONT][/COLOR]
[FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#cc66cc]Developers[/COLOR][/SIZE]
Develop new content for the community.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Their role is to develop new content for the servers or websites. This can include plugins, mods, web development and more. Furthermore, this may also include the alterations of current software to better integrate with the network. At some points, we may hire a freelance developer for a single project. Whereas other times we may use the same developer multiple times if they have proven their capability.[/FONT]
[/LIST]
[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#cc66cc]Graphic Artists[/COLOR][/SIZE]
Create new graphical designs for the community.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]Their role is to create new custom graphical content for our community. This includes various logos, banners, wallpapers and more. This rank may also work with many other Staff Members to provide graphical art for various community related events. As with our Developer role, our Graphic Artists are usually freelance and often are hired for one or two projects.[/FONT]
[/LIST]
[FONT=Trebuchet MS][SIZE=6][COLOR=#cc66cc][B]Affiliates[/B][/COLOR][/SIZE][/FONT]
[B][FONT=Trebuchet MS]These are some friends of ToastyNetworks.[/FONT][/B]
[LIST]
[*][FONT=Arial]This is less of a role, and more a rank which simply highlights our affiliated networks. The people with this rank work closely with our staff team to help engage in multi-community events and to provide support to each other when necessary.[/FONT]
[/LIST]
